## Cross-Cutting Influences

| Thinker | Relevance |
|---------|-----------|
| Kurt Lewin | Grandfather of OD and change. AA inherits the action research orientation but rejects the linear unfreeze-change-refreeze model. |
| John Kotter | The dominant change model AA challenges. Eight steps assume a known destination and linear execution. |
| Karl Weick | Sensemaking under ambiguity — essential for understanding adoption resistance. |
| W. Edwards Deming | Systems, not people, drive outcomes. |
| Nassim Nicholas Taleb | Antifragility. Systems that gain from disorder. Adaptive Adoption is designed to be antifragile. |
| Daniel Kahneman | Dual-process theory. The cognitive science foundation for Pillar 6. |
| Prosci / ADKAR | **The target.** Awareness + desire + knowledge ≠ action. The intention-action gap is real, and ADKAR has no mechanism for it. |

